Episode 16 Let us Go Hunting!
Wow, kewl!
Getting a small, quick rat into your Stand's range will be difficult,
but by using the bearings, your range will increase to about 20 meters.
This should be obvious, but it will not work against a Stand.
You will only be able to use it to defeat the user.
Try it.

I am not trying to put pressure on you, but remember that.

Apparently, Akira Otoishi shot the rat
near this irrigation canal.
Given the area, it was probably a brown rat.
Brown rats can swim, live anywhere, and eat anything.
The big ones reach about 20 to 30 centimeters long,
and some can weigh one kilogram.
They can jump about 2 meters.
Found it.
Are not those a bird's tracks?
Their front paws have four digits, and the back ones have five.

This line was made by its tail.
It is a rat that is around 20 centimeters long.
I am not sure how many, but they are definitely here.
There is a tick on this leaf.
That means rats come through here often.
Without a doubt, there is a nest deep in that drainage channel.
For now, we will set a trap here and video tape it.
That is one of those cameras that let you watch while you are taping, right?
You are not using cheese for the trap?
It is a crumb of tempura.
Cheese is too extravagant for rats.
There sure are a lot of flies...
Jotaro!
Th-This is...
Rat corpses?
It is exactly what it looks like!
It is like the jelly from stewed fish.
Why the heck are you poking at it?!

The flesh of these rats was melted once, then hardened again.

What do you even do to leave behind a corpse like this?
I am not sure...

It used its Stand?
It killed the others and made their territory its own.
Which means...
It is definitely making a nest at the end of this drainage channel.
But the question is
if something capable of doing this will just stay quiet.
Looks like the drainage channel leads to that farm.
We might already be too late.
R-Really?

There are no signs of life at the house, either.

The rat is there.
And just as I feared,
it is likely that the people living there have already been killed.
Let us go check out that house.
The rat will let us approach within a certain distance,
because it is confident that no slow human is going to catch it.
It is not expecting us to blast bearings at it.
That is how we will get close enough to nail it in one shot.
Found something.
Rat droppings.

It is meat.

Let us check it out.
Right.

What?!
There it is!
Damn it!
It is right there!

And...
Am I actually naIve enough to believe that?
This rat is a Stand user!
Jo

I need to put composure ahead of speed, right?
If I do not get it in one try, it will figure out my range.

Damn it...

Stay right there for a bit...

Now!
Crush

That shape...

Slap it away with my bare hands?

I got the rat!
It is over!
Jeez.

we may have a problem.
Huh?

I was just attacked by it.
Jotaro!
Y-Your hand...

some kind of Stand poison courses through you, melting even Stands.
Getting hit by five or six of those

Thank goodness I dodged!
I am lucky our personalities are so different.

What the hell is this?!

Star Platinum, The World!
Good grief.
Do not panic.

Halfway up the hill, near those three rocks.
You are amazing!
Both the rat and you, Jotaro!

Damn it!

I am going to get you, you little bastard.

I thought you would look if I missed, and face your body this way.
Now I can target you for sure.

The Stand rats that Akira Otoishi created...

I am not sure how to feel...

Good grief.
